Description: This lowered interest rate is the second time since last year. The interest rate reduction shows that the expenditure of consumers with the main driving force of economic growth is still sluggish, and people are increasingly worried that China has not rebounded as strong as expected after the cancellation of "clearing". Florence Lo/Reuters China's largest bank in China has lowered its deposit interest rate, hoping that consumers will change from savings to consumption.

